The same can be said for {{champion:106}}  and {{champion:92}} 
I tend to beat Riven in trades, but struggle in laning phase because if she "doesn't" trade with me, she has an easy time poking and escaping. I think the above matchup is similar. Atrox can "outplay" Darius even if he can't win a direct fight. How you play is a big factor

Other examples that I see might include Galio vs Ahri. He can completely out damage her, and out sustain her, but if he fails to land consistent skill shots, or Ahri utilises her mobility well to whittle down his hp, Galio can still lose either due to mana or just generally being outplayed. Winning hit for hit isn't the same as winning a lane, and teamfights is another story
